        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add core session goals",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Replaces #85723 with core-owned session goals instead of a plugin/lease extension surface.\n- Persists goals on `SessionEntry`, exposes `get_goal`/`create_goal`/`update_goal` model tools, and adds native/text `/goal` controls.\n- Adds resumable blocked/budget-limited goal behavior, projected session-row goal state, and a compact TUI footer goal indicator.\n- Adds a dedicated Goal docs page plus TUI/slash-command cross-links and focused regression coverage.\n\n## Verification\n\nBehavior addressed: Core-owned thread/session goals with model tools, `/goal` controls, TUI footer status, and dedicated docs, replacing plugin-owned PR #85723.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check ...` on touched TS/docs files\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs ...` on touched TS files\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx`\n- `pnpm format:docs:check`\n- `pnpm docs:check-links -- docs/tools/goal.md docs/tools/slash-commands.md docs/web/tui.md docs/cli/tui.md docs/tools/index.md`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm exec tsx -e ...` direct goal lifecycle, formatter, stale-baseline, budget-resume, and TUI session-refresh smokes\n- `/Users/steipete/Projects/agent-skills/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\nEvidence after fix: Formatting, oxlint, docs index, docs MDX, docs formatting, docs links, whitespace, direct TS smokes, and final local autoreview passed. Final autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nObserved result after fix: Goals persist in core session state; model tools can read/create/complete/block goals; `/goal` can start, show, pause, resume, complete, block, and clear goals; blocked goals can be resumed; budget-limited goals resume with a fresh budget window; stale token baselines are not overcounted; TUI session rows carry goal state and the footer shows compact goal status.\n\nWhat was not tested: Vitest wrapper did not complete in this checkout; it hung without test output and was stopped. Earlier broad `tsgo` was blocked on existing unrelated `src/config/io.ts` unique-symbol errors.\n",
